# Environment Configuration for NomNom

## How to set up

1. Copy this file to `.env` (don't commit .env to git!)
2. Fill in your Supabase credentials
3. Keep this file private and secure

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Supabase Setup Steps

1. Go to https://supabase.com
2. Create a new project
3. Get your credentials from Project Settings > API Keys
4. Fill in the values below

## Environment Variables

### Supabase Credentials
```
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGci...
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGci...
```

### iOS (.xcconfig format)
```swift
// In Xcode > Build Settings > User-Defined Settings
SUPABASE_URL = https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = eyJhbGci...
```

### Android (local.properties)
```properties
supabase.url=https://your-project.supabase.co
supabase.anonKey=eyJhbGci...
```

### Backend (if needed)
```
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGci...
```

## Security Notes

🔒 **NEVER commit .env or API keys to Git**
🔒 **Use Anon Key for mobile apps (with RLS)**
🔒 **Use Service Role Key only on backend servers**
🔒 **Enable Row Level Security on all tables**

